{"ts":"2026-06-26T00:08:58.230Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Integrating Command Center Button**\n\nI'm now integrating the search button within the existing header, placing it to the left of the \"Book a Consultation\" button for optimal visual hierarchy. I've designed a sleek, premium look for the button, including a subtle gradient and hover effects. The mobile implementation is also in progress. I will be sure to ensure that the mobile button is visually integrated with the existing mobile navigation, and opens the same command center. I'm now testing its responsiveness across different screen sizes.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T00:08:59.971Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Mobile Button Placement**\n\nI'm now implementing the mobile search button. After considering different locations, I've decided to place it right next to the burger menu icon within the header. This location is very clean, accessible, and intuitive for mobile users. Now I will focus on refining the button's appearance and ensuring it integrates seamlessly with the existing mobile navigation, matching the styling and theme. It must trigger the same Command Center as the desktop keyboard shortcut, of course.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T00:09:01.603Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Mobile Menu Button**\n\nI'm now implementing the mobile search button. I've placed the button alongside the burger menu, ensuring a clean and intuitive user experience. I'm focusing on seamless integration, matching the existing styling and theme, and ensuring it triggers the same Command Center as the desktop keyboard shortcut. I've written out keyboard accessibility requirements: focusing on using `useEffect` for keyboard event listeners. The event listener should be on the `document` with a keydown event that uses `cmd+k` or `ctrl+k`, which should use state hooks, and use the existing menu for mobile visibility.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
